{
  "texts": [
    "For this reason, we decided to use all the notes available to us.",
    "While we agree that we probably missed some of the events, especially since we took the pragmatic approach to reduce computational requirements for LLMs by using regular expressions to pre-screen the notes prior to LLM inference, we estimate recall (Table 1) and show that the recall was relatively high for most events in the analysis.In our study, we used EHR data from only one institution, and some statistical associations were weak because of a small number of detected events; thus, further work is needed to validate these models at other institutions and, preferably, other regions of the country.",
    "Our analysis did not include important covariates, such as socioeconomic status.",
    "It is well known that resources can buffer the negative effects of stress [52].",
    "This information is not routinely collected during the patient admission process and is usually not reflected in free-text notes, perhaps a proxy variable for socioeconomic status could be the type of insurance used or social vulnerability based on geocoded addresses."
  ]
}